\title{intraitR: Morphological Trait Analysis Toolkit for Freshwater Fish}
\description{
\code{intraitR} provides a coherent workflow for the analysis of morphological
traits in freshwater fish, from raw two-dimensional landmark digitization
to derived linear ratios and morphological space, together with tools to
quantify intraspecific morphological variability and measurement error.
}
\section{Workflow}{

The package is organised around five steps, each covered by one or more
functions:
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Import} raw landmark coordinates with \code{\link[=read_tps]{read_tps()}} or
\code{\link[=read_landmarks_csv]{read_landmarks_csv()}} (or simulate a data set with
\code{\link[=simulate_fish_landmarks]{simulate_fish_landmarks()}}).
\item \strong{Align} configurations with Generalised Procrustes Analysis
using \code{\link[=gpa_fish]{gpa_fish()}}, a thin wrapper around \code{\link[geomorph:gpagen]{geomorph::gpagen()}}.
\item \strong{Derive traits}: inter-landmark linear distances
(\code{\link[=linear_distances]{linear_distances()}}) and normalised morphological ratios
(\code{\link[=morpho_ratios]{morpho_ratios()}}); correct for allometry with
\code{\link[=correct_allometry]{correct_allometry()}} if required.
\item \strong{Explore shape}: build and plot a morphological space with
\code{\link[=morpho_space]{morpho_space()}}.
\item \strong{Assess variability and error}: quantify intraspecific
morphological variability with \code{\link[=intraspecific_variability]{intraspecific_variability()}} and
\code{\link[=itv_index]{itv_index()}}, measurement error / repeatability from replicated
digitization with \code{\link[=measurement_error]{measurement_error()}}, and landmark-level
digitization (operator) bias with \code{\link[=digitization_error]{digitization_error()}}.
}
}

\section{The FISHMORPH protocol}{

The package additionally implements the specific 21/22-landmark
digitization scheme and trait protocol of the FISHMORPH database
(Brosse et al., 2021): \code{\link[=fishmorph_segments]{fishmorph_segments()}} computes the 11 linear
measurements of the protocol (with automatic pixel-to-centimetre
conversion via an embedded scale bar), \code{\link[=fishmorph_ratios]{fishmorph_ratios()}} derives the
9 unitless FISHMORPH ratios (applying the special-case rules of
Villéger et al., 2010), \code{\link[=trait_space]{trait_space()}} builds a generic functional
trait space (PCA or PCoA) from any numeric trait table, and
\code{\link[=plot_fishmorph_points]{plot_fishmorph_points()}} / \code{\link[=simulate_fishmorph_points]{simulate_fishmorph_points()}} visualise and
simulate data following this scheme.
}

\section{Dependencies}{

The statistical core of the package (Procrustes superimposition, shape
PCA, Procrustes ANOVA and morphological disparity) is delegated to the
\pkg{geomorph} package, which is the reference implementation of these
methods for the R ecosystem (Adams, Collyer and Kaliontzopoulou, 2024).
\code{intraitR} focuses on fish-specific conveniences: reading digitization
files, computing ecomorphological ratios, and reporting intraspecific
variability and measurement error in a form directly usable in
ecological analyses.
}

